
'''= a Communications protocol for discovery of digital identity authentication services'''

URL = http://yadis.org/wiki/Main_Page

=Description=

From the Wikipedia article:

"Yadis is a Communications protocol for discovery of digital identity authentication services, such as OpenID, and related data sharing services. This allows digital identities to be composed from several different services, and lets Internet users define what information they expose to third parties.

Yadis sites take traditional URLs (web site addresses) as identifiers or "addresses" for the Yadis documents representing people and services."
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YADIS)


